---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import MobilityAssessment from '../../components/calculators/MobilityAssessment.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Mobility Assessment Tool"
  description="Assess your mobility and flexibility levels with our comprehensive mobility assessment tool. Designed specifically for men over 40 to identify areas needing attention."
>
  <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-8">
    <h2>Why Mobility Matters After 40</h2>
    <p>
      As we age, maintaining good mobility becomes increasingly important. Proper mobility not only helps prevent injuries
      but also improves workout performance and daily life quality. This assessment will help you identify areas that need
      attention and provide targeted recommendations.
    </p>
    
    <div class="my-6">
      <h3>Benefits of Good Mobility</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Injury Prevention:</strong> Reduces risk of strains and joint problems</li>
        <li><strong>Better Performance:</strong> Improves exercise form and effectiveness</li>
        <li><strong>Daily Function:</strong> Makes everyday movements easier</li>
        <li><strong>Pain Reduction:</strong> Helps alleviate common age-related discomfort</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <MobilityAssessment />

  <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mt-8">
    <div class="my-6 p-4 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg">
      <h3 class="mt-0">Understanding Your Assessment</h3>
      
      <h4>Score Interpretation</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Optimal:</strong> Excellent mobility for your age group</li>
        <li><strong>Functional:</strong> Adequate for most activities but room for improvement</li>
        <li><strong>Limited:</strong> Areas needing focused attention</li>
        <li><strong>Restricted:</strong> Significant mobility limitations to address</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Important Notes</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Results are age-adjusted for realistic expectations</li>
        <li>Focus on gradual improvement</li>
        <li>Always work within pain-free ranges</li>
        <li>Consider consulting a professional for severe restrictions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Improving Your Mobility</h2>

    <h3>Key Areas of Focus</h3>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Upper Body</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Shoulder mobility</li>
          <li>Thoracic spine flexibility</li>
          <li>Neck range of motion</li>
          <li>Wrist mobility</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Lower Body</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Hip mobility</li>
          <li>Ankle flexibility</li>
          <li>Knee stability</li>
          <li>Lower back health</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Implementation Strategies</h3>
    <div class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg">
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Daily Practice</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Morning mobility routine (5-10 minutes)</li>
        <li>Pre-workout mobility drills</li>
        <li>Evening stretching/recovery</li>
        <li>Movement breaks during long periods of sitting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900 p-4 rounded-lg mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 mt-0">Pro Tips for Success</h3>
      <ul class="text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200">
        <li>Consistency is more important than intensity</li>
        <li>Focus on quality of movement over range</li>
        <li>Use dynamic movements for warm-ups</li>
        <li>Static stretching is best post-workout or before bed</li>
        <li>Consider using mobility tools (foam rollers, bands)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <h3>When to Seek Professional Help</h3>
      <p>
        While this assessment provides valuable insights, consider consulting a professional if you:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Experience persistent pain during movements</li>
        <li>Have significant asymmetries in mobility</li>
        <li>Recently had surgery or injury</li>
        <li>Need specific guidance for your condition</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>
